<code><span style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 30px; color: red;">root@kali:&#126;#</span> <span style="font-size: 30px; color: green;">Whoami</span></code>
<br><br>
I’m penetration tester with a strong focus on offensive security, red teaming methodologies, and real-world attack simulation. With hands-on experience across enterprise environments, I specialize in identifying, 
exploiting, and helping remediate complex security vulnerabilities.
Currently working in a professional security role, I bring practical exposure to both Linux and Windows environments, with a particular interest in Active Directory exploitation, privilege escalation, and post-exploitation techniques. I approach security not just as a checklist, but as an attacker—thinking in paths, chains, and impact.

My work is deeply rooted in continuous learning and practical application. I actively solve labs, CTFs, and real-world scenarios to sharpen my skills and stay aligned with evolving threat landscapes. I also document my findings, techniques, and methodologies to build a structured knowledge base—both for personal mastery and to contribute back to the community.

 I break into systems (legally), build labs that simulate real enterprise misconfigurations, and automate the boring parts of red teaming so I can focus on the interesting ones.

